The paper proposes an unsupervised anomaly detection algorithm based on Variational AutoEncoders (VAE) for event sequence data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also addresses real-world problems such as error diagnosis and fraud detection, which are common in the Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a visualization system to support interactive exploration of the analysis result, which is relevant to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CR, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
